      <preface xml:id="preface">
        <title>About This Book</title>
        <p>
          This is a free textbook teaching introductory statistics for undergraduates in Psychology. 
          This textbook is part of a larger OER course package for teaching undergraduate statistics 
          in Psychology, including this textbook, a lab manual, and a course website. All of the 
          materials are free and copiable, with source code maintained in Github repositories.
        </p>
        <p>
          This textbook was primarily written by Matthew J. C. Crump. Two of the chapters were 
          adapted from Danielle Navarro's wonderful (and bigger) free textbook, also licensed 
          under the same creative commons license. Jeff Suzuki contributed the YouTube videos 
          peppered throughout the textbook.
        </p>
        <p>
          All resources are released under a creative commons license CC BY-SA 4.0.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          <alert>About This PreTeXt Version:</alert> This book has been converted to PreTeXt format 
          to make it more accessible and easier to use across different platforms. The original textbook 
          was written in R Markdown by Matthew J. C. Crump, Danielle J. Navarro, and Jeffrey Suzuki. 
          The full citation for the original work is: Crump, M. J. C., Navarro, D. J., <ampersand/> Suzuki, J. (2019, June 5). 
          Answering Questions with Data (Textbook): Introductory Statistics for Psychology Students. 
          <url href="https://doi.org/10.17605/OSF.IO/JZE52" visual="doi.org/10.17605/OSF.IO/JZE52"/>
        </p>
        
        <p>
          The original source code is available at 
          <url href="https://github.com/CrumpLab/statistics" visual="github.com/CrumpLab/statistics"/>, 
          and the original online textbook can be found at 
          <url href="https://crumplab.github.io/statistics/" visual="crumplab.github.io/statistics"/>.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          The source code for this PreTeXt version is maintained at 
          <url href="https://github.com/PreTeXtBooks/statistics" visual="github.com/PreTeXtBooks/statistics"/>. 
          If you encounter any issues with this version, please report them at 
          <url href="https://github.com/PreTeXtBooks/statistics/issues" visual="github.com/PreTeXtBooks/statistics/issues">the issues page</url>.
        </p>
      </preface>
